description:
&lt;p&gt;** 14 month Fixed Term Contract - Apprenticeship **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from individuals wishing to become an Apprentice and gain experience in the NHS. You will develop new skills and knowledge whilst working with an established team gaining valuable work experience and a recognised apprenticeship qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be enrolled with a local education provider and will be required to complete your Level 2 Customer Service Practitioner Apprenticeship Programme within the duration of the placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an apprentice to join the Sir Thomas Browne Library Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sir Thomas Library is a busy and interesting work environment based in Centre Block Level 1, Norfolk and Norwich Hospital. The Library team provides a high quality, comprehensive and efficient Library and information service to NHS staff and students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a team and respect and integrity are an essential part of the ethos of working together that drives our department. This is a customer-focused role with varying demands, so building an effective rapport with colleagues and being ready to take their guidance and offer your support will be really important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will involve a variety of customer-focused activities such as staffing the main enquiry desk, issuing and returning books, looking after Library stock and general Library administrative tasks. You will be a first point of contact for a range of customer enquiries (with support from the team) and will also participate in marketing and promotion of Library services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take PRIDE in our work for the NNUH and hope that in your application you will show us how you take PRIDE in your work too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monday – Thursday 9.00-5.30, Friday 9.00-5.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants must be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aged 16+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resident in the UK/EEA for the last three years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must not have a Degree, Level 4 qualification or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must NOT be in any form of formal government-funded education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good general standard of education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 GCSE’s at Grade D/3 or above (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good standard of literacy and numeracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The NNUH are pleased to be able to offer a variety of challenging apprenticeships. Should you be selected for interview we may wish to discuss with you a range of alternative positions for you to consider.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Full time: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: &lt;/strong&gt;17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications: &lt;/strong&gt;29th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications: &lt;/strong&gt;8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kim Barker-Ottley - Library and Knowledge Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
